Dear all,
There are only a few seats available for our online course Generalized Linear Models in R, taking place from 25?29 May.
 
Many statistical methods commonly taught as separate tools (t-tests, ANOVA, regression) are in fact part of a single, powerful framework: Generalized Linear Models (GLMs). This course presents GLMs as a unified and practical approach for analysing real biological and experimental data in R, including Gaussian, binary, and count data.
 
During the course, you will learn how to:
Fit and interpret GLMs in R (including logistic and Poisson regression)
Work with categorical and continuous predictors
Understand model selection and diagnostic approaches
Visualize and effectively communicate model results
Build a strong foundation for advanced methods such as mixed models, GAMs, and Bayesian approaches
 
